<TITLE> Disney may up stake in India's UTV Software: paper </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MUMBAI , Feb 17 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The Walt Disney Co is plans to increase its stake in Indian media firm UTV Software Communications Ltd to 32 percent, the Business Standard Newspaper reported on Sunday. The deal is estimated to be worth 13 billion rupees ($328 million), the paper said, quoting unnamed sources. UTV officials were not available for comment on the deal, but the company, which produces movies and television content, is scheduled to make a "strategic announcement" on Monday morning. According to data from the Bombay Stock exchange website, Walt Disney Co currently holds 14.85 percent in the Indian firm. Founders now hold 30.67 percent in the company. Disney will also buy 15 percent in UTV's broadcasting unit, which is likely to launch an English business news channel, the paper said. In 2006, Disney acquired Hindi-language kids-entertainment channel Hungama, from UTV. On Friday, UTV shares closed 9.3 percent higher at 862.50 rupees in a strong Mumbai market, valuing the Indian firm at nearly 20 billion rupees
